 your file","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":140.08,"end":140.52,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_05","text":"Absolutely","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":140.94,"end":141.38,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_00","text":"Thanks","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":142.26,"end":152.32,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_03","text":"Okay that's it Thank you Angela for giving me the time I will leave the meeting now Have a good day everyone Maria Ken good luck with your training","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":153.62,"end":156.08,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_01","text":"Thanks Tarek Speak to you soon Thanks","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":156.28,"end":156.72,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_00","text":"Thanks","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":156.72,"end":157.04,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_06","text":"Bye","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":157.04,"end":157.9,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_07","text":"Great","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":158.36,"end":229.78,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_01","text":"So let's get back to our business Maria and Ken you were both hired for the customer care positions This means that you'll deal with our clients team leads and other companies who have purchased our software You will answer some of their questions or provide a short demo of how our software and its features work First let me tell you a little bit about our product and our company Then we'll go through your duties and responsibilities And finally you can ask me questions if you have any Sounds good So the two owners Jen and Nina created our company three years ago They created software for training work teams called Logiteam It became an instant success and now we have 43 employees 82 customers and five different product packages Our product is simple to use with some training and that's where you come into the picture In the next two weeks you'll become experts of Logiteam We'll make sure that you're familiar with all basic functions security features add ons and the most common glitches too By the end of this training you'll be able to assist our clients with using the software to its full potential Do you guys have any questions so far","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":230.66,"end":235.66,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_00","text":"Yes I have a question Do we use our own devices or the company's laptop during the training","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true},{"start":236.52,"end":258.18,"kind":"orphan","speakerId":null,"localLabel":"SPEAKER_L_01","text":"Great question You don't need your own device We will set up your account on the computer you'll be using for work so it's better to start working on that Great thanks I have a question Will I be interacting with clients over the phone or video conference We use a video conferencing tool that will be covered during your training Okay thank you","source":"speaker","editSource":"AUTO","manuallyEdited":false,"named":false,"orphan":true}],"summary":"Summary of the meeting\n\n- Purpose and participants: The session introduced two new hires, Ken and Maria, to the Lock A customer care team. Tarek from customer care (and briefly, Maria from HR) joined to outline onboarding and training. Angela moderated the meeting.\n\n- Onboarding and required forms: Tarek explained that to begin work, Ken and Maria must sign a liability policy and confidentiality agreement (electronically) and send the signed document to him. The form requires four initials and two signatures. Access to work depends on having the signed document on file. Tarek will resend the documents if needed, and Ken was asked to email him to verify his address.\n\n- Roles and training plan: Ken and Maria will handle client inquiries, team leads, and other companies using Logiteam, including short demos of the software. Over the next two weeks, they will become experts on Logiteam, covering basic functions, security features, add-ons, and common glitches to help clients maximize the software.\n\n- Product context: The product is Logiteam, developed by owners Jen and Nina. The company has grown to 43 employees, 82 customers, and five product packages. The training aims to prepare new hires to assist clients effectively.\n\n- Practical questions and next steps: \n  - Devices: new hires will use company-provided devices; no personal devices needed during training.\n  - Access setup: accounts will be created on the company computer used for work.\n  - Communication tool: a video conferencing tool will be used for client interactions and will be covered in training.\n  - Action items: Tarek to ensure the liability/confidentiality documents are sent and signed; Ken to email Tarek to verify contact details.\n\n- Closing: Angela wrapped up and wished Ken and Maria good luck with their training.","title":"Onboarding and Training for New Customer Care Team","transcript":"Thank you all for joining. If you haven't met yet, we have our two newly hired customer care team members, Ken and Maria. Hi, guys. Welcome to the team. Thanks, Angela. It's great to be here. Hi, everyone. And Tarek from the customer care team. Maria from human resources is joining us for a brief period of time. Hi, Tarek. Morning, everyone. I scheduled this meeting to introduce our new team members to our training process. Tarek requested to be part of this meeting because he has some information for you as well. Tarek, would you like to begin? Sure. Thank you, Angela. So Maria, Ken, welcome to Lock A team. I want to talk to you about some forms that you need to fill out before you can begin work. You have received an email last week with our liability policy and our confidentiality agreement. The one about you agreeing not to share any confidential information about our company with any third parties. Have you received it? Yes, I have. I don't think I received that. I'm sorry. No problem. I will send it to you today. Once you have the document, please read it carefully and sign electronically. There are four places where you will need to insert your initials and two where we need your signature. Once signed and saved, please send the document directly to me. My email address is Tarek.godas at mail.ca. That is T-A-R-E-K dot G-U-L-D-U-Z at mail.ca. This is very important because you cannot work until I have the signed document on file. Do you have any questions? No, I'll send it to you this afternoon. Perfect. Thank you. Ken, please send me an email so I can double check the email address I have in your file. Absolutely. Thanks. Okay, that's it. Thank you, Angela, for giving me the time. I will leave the meeting now. Have a good day, everyone. Maria, Ken, good luck with your training. Thanks, Tarek. Speak to you soon. Thanks. Thanks. Bye. Great. So let's get back to our business. Maria and Ken, you were both hired for the customer care positions. This means that you'll deal with our clients, team leads, and other companies who have purchased our software. You will answer some of their questions or provide a short demo of how our software and its features work. First, let me tell you a little bit about our product and our company. Then we'll go through your duties and responsibilities. And finally, you can ask me questions if you have any. Sounds good. So the two owners, Jen and Nina, created our company three years ago. They created software for training work teams called Logiteam. It became an instant success, and now we have 43 employees, 82 customers, and five different product packages. Our product is simple to use with some training, and that's where you come into the picture. In the next two weeks, you'll become experts of Logiteam. We'll make sure that you're familiar with all basic functions, security features, add-ons, and the most common glitches too. By the end of this training, you'll be able to assist our clients with using the software to its full potential. Do you guys have any questions so far? Yes, I have a question. Do we use our own devices or the company's laptop during the training? Great question. You don't need your own device. We will set up your account on the computer you'll be using for work, so it's better to start working on that. Great, thanks. I have a question. Will I be interacting with clients over the phone or video conference? We use a video conferencing tool that will be covered during your training. Okay, thank you.","transcriptChunks":[{"start":12.420000076293945,"end":15.859999656677246,"text":"Thank you all for joining.","words":[{"start":12.420000076293945,"end":12.880000114440918,"text":"Thank"},{"start":12.880000114440918,"end":13.34000015258789,"text":"you"},{"start":13.34000015258789,"end":13.34000015258789,"text":"all"},{"start":13.34000015258789,"end":15.5600004196167,"text":"for"},{"start":15.5600004196167,"end":15.859999656677246,"text":"joining"}]},{"start":16.440000534057617,"end":22.15999984741211,"text":"If you haven't met yet, we have our two newly hired customer care team members, Ken and Maria.","words":[{"start":16.440000534057617,"end":16.540000915527344,"text":"If"},{"start":16.540000915527344,"end":16.719999313354492,"text":"you"},